%% Diagram: Read-your-writes pattern in eventually-consistent systems
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant API as API
    participant W as Write Store
    participant B as Event Broker
    participant R as Read Store

    Note over U,R: Naive flow — user sees stale read
    U->>API: PUT /profile (write)
    API->>W: persist
    W-->>API: ok
    API->>B: publish ProfileUpdated
    API-->>U: 200 OK
    U->>API: GET /profile (read)
    API->>R: query
    R-->>API: stale value
    API-->>U: stale data 😕

    Note over U,R: Mitigation — read-your-writes via session token
    U->>API: PUT /profile (write)
    API->>W: persist
    W-->>API: write_version=v42
    API->>B: publish ProfileUpdated
    API-->>U: 200 OK + write_version=v42
    U->>API: GET /profile (If-Min-Version: v42)
    API->>R: query, ensure version >= v42
    alt projection caught up
        R-->>API: fresh value (v42)
        API-->>U: fresh data
    else projection lagging
        API->>W: fall back to write store
        W-->>API: fresh value
        API-->>U: fresh data
    end
